table-0762-912.caption: Classification
data: Blade points down and "cutting edge" faces away from the fencer's chest side. To stop low-line cut to chest.
Blade down and to the outside, wrist pronated.
Arm half-extended laterally, blade pointing forward with downward incline, cutting edge facing away fencer's flank side. To stop low-line cut to flank.
Blade up and to the outside, wrist pronated. Not often used in Foil, and in Épée only as a block to wrist flicks.

Standard en garde but rotated so cutting edge faces further in the flank direction, i.e. guard kept low, sword upright with a slight forward tilt, cutting edge facing 45° to the flank side. To stop high-line cut to flank.
Similar to tierce on the chest side or prime flipped upside-down; guard low, cutting edge facing away from chest, sword upright with slight chest-direction tilt. To stop high-line cut to chest.
Blade up and to the inside, wrist pronated. Not often used in Foil or Épée
Blade held up almost horizontally with bent arm, cutting edge facing upward and forward, blade has a slight tilt meaning that the point is higher than the guard. To stop cut to head.

Blade up and to the outside, wrist supinated. This parry can be Lateral or Circular. The Lateral Parry is from Quarte to Sixte. The Circular Parry, also known as "Counter Sixte", is a D shaped parry, dropping the points and bringing it up on the inside bringing your point back towards your En Guard line.

The arm position is a mirror image of quinte (supinated, forearm vertical on the quarte side of the head). Point is diagonal across the body covering the head, but towards the opponent, and slightly upwards (or forwards for a direct riposte in opposition). To stop cut to head.
Blade down and to the inside, wrist supinated. Point dropped, the wrist is in the same place as in Quarte. This parry is semi-circular, the point is dropped from Quarte to Septime (or the opposite).
Very similar to Tierce, but the blade is held upside down, with the palm facing and being level with the temple. To stop cut to the flank and back.
Blade down and to the outside, wrist supinated. Point is dropped, the wrist is in the same place as in Sixte. This parry is semi-circular, the point is dropped from Sixte to Octave (or the opposite).

The tip of the blade is on the inside and dropped as in Septime, while the hand is raised. For this reason, Neuvieme is sometimes referred to as "high septime". This parry is often used to sweep through the upper lines of the fencers target, or as a ceding parry.

data: Hawthorn lost by nine points after leading at one stage throughout the match.
Hawthorn suffered its first loss against Collingwood since 2006 and Lance Franklin was reported for bumping.

A narrow win over Richmond who at the time was at the bottom of the ladder. The match was not decided until the final five minutes.
Despite the Swans scoring one goal more than Hawthorn, two late behinds saw Hawthorn win. Again, Lance Franklin is suspended for high head contact.
Hawthorn defeated a disappointing Port Adelaide by 11 points to register its fourth consecutive victory.
A big win over the struggling Crows saw the Hawks register its fifth win in succession.
A late goal from Lance Franklin got the Hawks home by just three points.
The Hawks led all day but succumbed in the last quarter. They missed some opportunities in the third quarter. Lance Franklin was the lead-goalkicker for Hawthorn.
Hawthorn defeated Lions by 75 points, handing Brisbane its eleventh defeat out of 12 games. Jarryd Roughead and Jordan Lewis each kicked 4 goals.
Hawthorn lost by eight points after having led for the majority of the contest.
Sydney played a dominant first half. Hawthorn made a small comeback, but the closest they got to Sydney was 23 points. Lance Franklin kicked four goals, the most in the Hawthorn side.
The Hawks broke free from the Demons during the last quarter to run away with a 21-point win to keep their finals hopes alive as well as end Melbourne's.

Hawthorn comfortably beat a Fremantle team which, having already clinched a finals berth, rested seven of its star players. The final margin was 116 points. Lance Franklin registered 5 goals for the Hawks.
Hawthorn trailed towards the end of the match, but took the lead from about 22 minutes into the last quarter.

table-0762-366.caption: Write Amplification Factors
data: The efficiency of the algorithm used to pick the next best block to erase and rewrite
The percentage of physical capacity which is allocated to the SSD controller (and not given to the user)

These commands must be sent by the operating system (OS) which tells the storage device which sectors contain invalid data. SSDs consuming these commands can then reclaim the pages containing these sectors as free space when the blocks containing these pages are erased instead of copying the invalid data to clean pages.
The percentage of the user capacity free of actual user data; requires TRIM, otherwise the SSD gains no benefit from any free user capacity
Erases all user data and related metadata which resets the SSD to the initial out-of-box performance (until garbage collection resumes)
The efficiency of the algorithm that ensures every block is written an equal number of times to all other blocks as evenly as possible
Grouping data based on how often it tends to change
In theory, sequential writes have a write amplification of 1, but other factors will still affect the value
Writing to non-sequential LBAs will have the greatest impact on write amplification
Write amplification goes down and SSD speed goes up when data compression and deduplication eliminates more redundant data.

This writes data at a rate of one bit per cell instead of the designed number of bits per cell (normally two bits per cell) to speed up reads and writes. Unfortunately, this at least doubles the write amplification because one cell will contain one bit instead of two or more bits per cell. Also, if capacity limits are approached, the SSD must rewrite the data written in SLC mode into MLC mode to free up space to accept more data.

data: Welcome to the Dream Chronicles, where the lines between reality and fantasy no longer exist. Follow subtle clues to help Faye find her missing husband and escape the mysterious sleeping spell that has taken over the town of Wish. Stay sharp and focused and you may unravel this intriguing, dreamy mystery!

Locked away within the Ancients' Place by Lilith, Fairy Queen of Dreams, Faye continues her quest to reunite with her beloved husband, Fidget. Navigate this stunning story world of intricate puzzles and magical landscapes as you unravel the secrets of your family's past in this alluring sequel. Dream Chronicles 2 takes you deeper into the Dream Realm than ever before with over 80 engaging puzzles offering all-new challenges and longer gameplay.

Unlock the secrets of the mysterious fairy realm in the third installment of the award-winning Dream Chronicles series, The Chosen Child. Discover hidden clues and challenging puzzles as you join Faye on her quest to save her daughter from the clutches of Lilith and reveal the secret prophecy of the Chosen Child in this all-new hidden object adventure with unexpected twists.

The epic Dream Chronicles saga continues in PlayFirst's award-winning adventure series. Play as Lyra, Faye's daughter, who finds herself trapped in a strange dimension on the day before her 18th birthday. Following clues sent by her grandfather, she flies across the realm in search of the Clockmaker who will help her restore time and return home. Solve intriguing puzzles and search for items that will reunite Lyra with family and friends in The Book of Air!

The award-winning adventure by PlayFirst continues in the most suspenseful chapter of the Dream Chronicles saga. A devastating storm has hit the village of Wish. Play as Lyra, and find a way to lift the evil curse. Embark on a quest to solve challenging puzzles and seek answers to save Lyra hometown in The Book of Water.
